pageContext.claim: “And young kids, if you have kids, I mean, it's incredible. Their immune system is stronger, who would have thought. And the younger the better. But they have statistics where a certain state had many thousands of deaths, thousands of deaths and not one death under 18. Think of it. Not one.”
pageContext.analysis: It's unclear what state Trump is talking about. Previously he has pointed to New Jersey, claiming there was only one death under age 18 -- not true -- but the fact remains that covid-19 can be deadly to people under age 18.
